Reminder to #MendocinoComplex and #PawneeFire survivors – the deadline to submit to participate in the @CalRecycle wildfire debris removal program is this Friday, September 28! Read more here: http://recovery.lakecountyca.gov/News/CalRecycle091718.htm

The #MendocinoComplex started in July 2018. It burned 459,123 acres in Colusa County, Lake County, Mendocino County and Glenn County, California. It is the largest wildfire in California history. https://bit.ly/2nigcic #CalWildfires #USwildfires @CAL_FIRE @R5_Fire_News
